# hype-frog runtime configuration (copy to `.env` — never commit real secrets)
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PageSpeed Insights (PSI)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REST API key from Google Cloud Console. Enable the "PageSpeed Insights API"
# for the key's project. Used only when the crawl prompts allow PSI (non-zero
# max PSI URLs). Leave unset to skip PSI calls (scores default to 0 in the workbook).
#
# Required IAM: none beyond API enablement; restrict the key by HTTP referrer or
# IP in production per your security policy.
#
# PSI_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Search Console (GSC)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GSC is loaded from OAuth **files**, not from this `.env` file:
#   - Default paths (relative to the `hype_frog` package root): `client_secrets.json`
#     (OAuth 2.0 Client ID, type "Desktop app") and `token.json` (refreshed user token).
#   - Place or symlink those files next to the installed package (e.g. under `src/hype_frog/`
#     in a source checkout). Paths are ignored by git — see `.gitignore`.
#
# OAuth scope used in code (read-only Search Console):
#   https://www.googleapis.com/auth/webmasters.readonly
#
# The authenticated Google account must have access to the Search Console property
# that matches the crawl target (URL prefix or domain property). Service-account
# JSON is not used by the current implementation; use the Desktop OAuth flow.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Override default Excel output path/filename for a run (otherwise auto-generated).
# HF_OUTPUT_FILENAME=
